  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I got there physically by boat.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I left [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] West Point and went down to [PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] the Pier 80 and got on the [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And that boat took me and 10,000 others on over to England.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Actually, I think we stopped in Gourock, Scotland, and then went by train from there down to [INAUDIBLE] in the south of England.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[INTERPOSING VOICES]",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was ordered.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I received orders to join headquarters US Third Army in Europe.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that came about, I think, through the interests of one of my classmates, who had also been instructed at West Point while I was there, by the name of Colonel [?",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "EM ?] [?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "O'Connell. ?] He was in the judge advocate's section of headquarters Third Army.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the judge advocate of Third Army was Colonel Charles E.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Cheever, whom I had known and whom had been an acting professor of law at West Point when I was there teaching.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So I knew Colonel Cheever and Colonel O'Connell.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they asked for my services in Headquarters Third Army.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So that's how I got there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I knew it would be something in the Administration of Military Justice, because I had done a terrific amount of trial work, not only down at my father's office, but when I got to West Point, I think they tallied it up, out of 97 court-martial cases that they had-- and these did not include-- it did include-- but the 97 cases really were involving the soldiers who were manning the detachments, like the field-artillery detachment, the infantry detachment.",
      "word_count": 79
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In other words, they had detachments of every branch of the service there-- stationed there at West Point.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they had their problems, of course.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
